# Stored procedures

## Naming

- Procedures use prefix `<DbPrefix>` and PascalCase segments, for example `<DbPrefix>User_GetAll`.
- Script files live under `Database/Scripts/` and should match or document deployed procedure names.

## Calling from C#

- Use fully qualified names: `"<DbSchema>.<DbPrefix>..."`.
- Create commands with `StoredProcedureHelper.CreateCommand(connection, "<DbSchema>.<DbPrefix>...", transaction?)`.
- Avoid raw SQL strings for procedure calls unless intentionally migrating away from stored procedures.

```csharp
using var command = StoredProcedureHelper.CreateCommand(_connection, "<DbSchema>.<DbPrefix>Role_GetAll");
```

- When adding a new procedure, add the `.sql` script under `Database/Scripts/` and reference the same fully qualified name in the service layer.
